<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>They starred together on a cult classic Halloween flick nearly 25 years ago.</p>

<p>And Sarah Jessica Parker, Bette Midler and Kathy Najimy are joining forces once again for a virtual Hocus Pocus reunion.</p>

<p>The women are getting into the spooky season to benefit Bette's annual fundraising gala for The New York Restoration Project, with this year's theme: In Search of the Sanderson Sisters: A Hocus Pocus Hulaween Takeover. </p>

<p>They're back! Sarah Jessica Parker, Bette Midler and Kathy Najimy are joining forces once again for a virtual Hocus Pocus reunion</p>

<p>Hocus Pocus was released on July 16, 1993 and followed the Sanderson Sisters who come back from the dead and terrorize a Salem, Massachusetts on Halloween.</p>

<p>The annual fundraiser will be hosted online this year and boasts 'one of the hottest pandemic-safe Halloween events of the year.'</p>

<p>Virtual classes are available at the Sanderson Sisters Charm School and guests can purchase exclusive merchandise.</p>

<p>Fun! The women are getting into the spooky season to benefit Bette's annual fundraising gala for The New York Restoration Project , with this year's theme: In Search of the Sanderson Sisters: A Hocus Pocus Hulaween Takeover</p>

<p>Youth: Hocus Pocus was released on July 16, 1993 and followed the Sanderson Sisters who come back from the dead and terrorize a small New England town on Halloween</p>

<p>Midler shared the news on her Instagram account with a post captioned: Come on in and take a look around...we're creepin' it real for the season.'   </p>

<p>Entertainment Tonight caught up with Midler and Najimy at last year's festivities and asked about their involvement in the upcoming Disney+ sequel.</p>

<p>'Oh my goodness me. Oh I hope they get to me before I'm a corpse,' Midler joked.  'We wanna fly again. I hope Disney+ is a big success and I hope we get to do it, because [Winifred] is of course one of my favorite characters.' </p>

<p>Best in the biz: The annual fundraiser will be hosted online this year and boasts 'one of the hottest pandemic-safe Halloween events of the year'</p>

<p>Sister act: Sarah also worked with Bette on the 1995 film The First Wives Club; seen in 2019</p>

<p>'Here's the honest answer: Sarah and Bette and I all have a million projects and things that we're into, so I don't know if they're gonna offer us [roles],' Najimy said at last year's event</p>

<p>When news began circulating about the potential reunion, Najimy was hesitant about how the women would be included. </p>

<p>'Here's the honest answer: Sarah and Bette and I all have a million projects and things that we're into, so I don't know if they're gonna offer us [roles],' she said. 'I don't know if the worlds are going to collide so that we could all three do it at the same time.</p>

<p>'But I'm happy that it's happening, because the fans are really rabid and they really want it,' she added with a smile. '[And] if we're not all available to star in it, I think it would be so great to do a cameo. I think that'd be really fun.'</p>
